
OOL - Open Optimization Library
===============================

The OOL is a library of local optimization methods for constrained
minimization problems that follows the standards of th GSL (GNU
Scientifc Library).

OOL is free software, you can redistribute it and/or modify it under
the terms of the GNU General Public License.

The GNU General Public License does not permit this software to be
redistributed in proprietary programs.

This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful, but
WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

Availability
============

The current (unstable) version of OOL is available from 
sourceforge.net/projects/ool

